
<html>
<h1 align="center">
HTML form exercise
</h1>
<p>
<font color = "red"> Please note: </font color> This example demonstrates how HTML forms can be used. Submit buttons should submit and reset button should reset the form.
</p>

<form name="contact form" font="timesnewroman">
<pre> <b>
       Contact form </b>
Your name*:   <input type="text" name="your name">
E-mail*:      <input type= "text" name ="email">
Phone number: <input type="text" name="phone">
Website*:     <input type="text" name="website" value="http://" columns="25">


Comments*:
<textarea name="comments" rows="5" cols="50"></textarea>

<b>
Text field </b>
Your name:    <input type="text" name="name">

<b>
Password field </b>
Password:     <input type="password" name="pwd">

<b>
Radio buttons </b>
Do you like pizza?
<input type="radio" name="pizza" value="yes" > Yes
<input type="radio" name="pizza" value="no"> No
<input type="radio" name="pizza" value="maybe"> Maybe
<input type="radio" name="pizza" value="never tried"> Never tried

<b>
check box</b>
<input type="checkbox" name="check"> check this box if you like our service?

<b>
Text area </b> 
Anything you would like to say?
<textarea name="say" rows="5" cols="40"> </textarea>

<b>
I Like </b>

<select name="toppings" multiple>
  <option value="mushrooms">mushrooms</option>
  <option value="green peppers">green peppers</option>
  <option value="onions">onions</option>
  <option value="tomatoes">tomatoes</option>
  <option value="olives">olives</option>
</select>

<b>
Menu</b>
Your favourite color:
<select name="color">
  <option value="red">red</option>
  <option value="green ">green</option>
  <option value="orange">orange</option>
  <option value="blue">blue</option>
  <option value="yellow">yellow</option>
</select>

<b>
Attach file </b>
<input type="text" name="file"> <input type="button" value="browse...">

<b>
Buttons</b>
<button type="submit" value="Submit">Submit</button> <button type="reset" value="Reset">Reset</button>
</form>
</html>

